WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.000
Good afternoon, my name is Evgenia Varlamova.

00:08.000 --> 00:12.000
I have 15 years of experience in the field of staff management

00:12.000 --> 00:15.000
and have successfully implemented projects in such companies as

00:15.000 --> 00:18.000
Eastline, Domodedovo International Airport,

00:18.000 --> 00:20.000
Azon Internet Store,

00:20.000 --> 00:23.000
and the international IT company CarTech Limited.

00:23.000 --> 00:26.000
At the moment, I work as a Director of the Investment and Financial Group

00:26.000 --> 00:29.000
Broker Credit Service.

00:29.000 --> 00:32.000
I am pleased to present to you the topic

00:32.000 --> 00:36.000
of the Corporate Training Center as a tool for planning a career.

00:36.000 --> 00:41.000
As you know, our managers and investors are so advanced

00:41.000 --> 00:46.000
that arguments on how to manage staff that are only in the plane

00:46.000 --> 00:50.000
of increasing salaries and material motivation, social packages,

00:50.000 --> 00:52.000
no longer work.

00:53.000 --> 00:58.000
Our management is interested in soft tools for motivating and

00:58.000 --> 01:05.000
maintaining staff, such as training, planning a career.

01:05.000 --> 01:09.000
This argument now works very well for both employees

01:09.000 --> 01:13.000
and candidates whom we want to involve in the company.

01:13.000 --> 01:17.000
Unfortunately, business is growing slower than the level of

01:17.000 --> 01:22.000
labor payment in Russia, and therefore we really do not even have a way out,

01:22.000 --> 01:27.000
except to apply soft tools in maintaining and attracting staff.

01:27.000 --> 01:32.000
In my experience, candidates talk less about the possibilities of

01:32.000 --> 01:37.000
salaries, social packages, planned increases.

01:37.000 --> 01:40.000
They rather talk about the career,

01:40.000 --> 01:44.000
about the positions that they will occupy from the very beginning

01:44.000 --> 01:51.000
and what opportunities they will have in terms of responsibility and growth.

01:51.000 --> 01:57.000
What opportunities in terms of career the company offers them for the next six months,

01:57.000 --> 02:01.000
a year, two years and a more distant future.

02:01.000 --> 02:04.000
It is how we will build the career of our employees,

02:04.000 --> 02:07.000
show them the horizons of their growth in our company.

02:07.000 --> 02:11.000
It is from this that it depends how much money we will really spend on our employees,

02:12.000 --> 02:22.000
what salary level we will offer them and how long we will successfully cooperate with our employees.

02:22.000 --> 02:29.000
Today we will talk about how we can plan the career of employees in our company

02:29.000 --> 02:35.000
and how career planning corresponds to all other functions of staff management.

02:35.000 --> 02:41.000
Today we will focus on the training center, the corporate university

02:41.000 --> 02:49.000
and all possible methods of training staff as the main mechanism for career development.

02:49.000 --> 02:55.000
I will tell you a little about the company in which we have promoted this project the most,

02:55.000 --> 03:02.000
about the career planning itself, what it consists of and about the system of the corporate university,

03:02.000 --> 03:10.000
how the corporate university and all methods of training and development of staff can work on career planning.

03:10.000 --> 03:20.000
In my experience, it is in high-tech companies that candidates and employees pay special attention to their career growth opportunities.

03:20.000 --> 03:26.000
We mean not only horizontal development, which is most often limited,

03:26.000 --> 03:37.000
but also flat organizational structure, in which there are only a few levels, 3, 4, 5 levels.

03:37.000 --> 03:43.000
Thus, the vertical opportunities for career growth are quite limited.

03:43.000 --> 03:48.000
Thus, each HR receives such a creative task,

03:48.000 --> 03:53.000
in the same way, without violating the organizational structure of the company,

03:53.000 --> 03:58.000
to show each employee the opportunities for professional growth

03:58.000 --> 04:05.000
and motivate him with the content of work, not only with salary and the name of positions.

04:10.000 --> 04:13.000
So, the main principles of career planning.

04:14.000 --> 04:19.000
We in the company declare the value of training and development of staff.

04:19.000 --> 04:24.000
Moreover, these positions can be described from the job offer,

04:24.000 --> 04:28.000
that is, even before a person becomes our employee.

04:28.000 --> 04:34.000
In the proposal for work, we prescribe not only the compensation package,

04:34.000 --> 04:39.000
but also pay special attention to the opportunities for training an employee,

04:39.000 --> 04:42.000
the opportunities for his career growth.

04:42.000 --> 04:47.000
And with some candidates, we are already at the stage of negotiations,

04:47.000 --> 04:59.000
until the candidate is our employee, we agree on what real promotion in his position he can get during the first year of work.

04:59.000 --> 05:05.000
For a longer term, our candidates in Russia do not often look,

05:05.000 --> 05:12.000
but it is very important for them that we, as a company, can offer them during the first year of work,

05:12.000 --> 05:21.000
if our cooperation develops positively, we will be satisfied with the employee and he will be satisfied with his work.

05:21.000 --> 05:25.000
It is very important at the stage of the interview with the candidate,

05:25.000 --> 05:31.000
when we are not yet associated with any official obligations to each other, to find out the level of his ambitions.

05:31.000 --> 05:37.000
It is at this moment that we can expect that the candidate will be able to reveal his ambitions and interests more,

05:37.000 --> 05:41.000
since he is not yet bound by any labor relations with the employer.

05:41.000 --> 05:46.000
It is at this moment that it is important to identify and concretize his ambitions,

05:46.000 --> 05:55.000
because if we take an employee with high ambitions for a position that does not imply serious career growth,

05:55.000 --> 06:00.000
then we will lose the company's money and lose the time of the employee.

06:00.000 --> 06:06.000
Thus, it is very important to discuss many psychological details at the time of the interview,

06:06.000 --> 06:14.000
which will show us how the career of this employee in the company can be successful.

06:14.000 --> 06:20.000
For example, we consider a candidate for the position of an accountant,

06:20.000 --> 06:26.000
but during the interview he tells us about his professional dreams in the field of finance,

06:26.000 --> 06:33.000
he wants to be a financial analyst, and in 5-10 years he wants to take the position of a financial director.

06:33.000 --> 06:39.000
And we understand that in the next two years he will hardly be able to get such a promotion in the company,

06:39.000 --> 06:44.000
so it is better to tell the candidate about this at the stage of the interview,

06:44.000 --> 06:50.000
and to look for a candidate for this position, who has less ambitions,

06:50.000 --> 06:59.000
and with whom we will have less headaches as soon as he takes this position and joins our company in labor relations.

06:59.000 --> 07:07.000
The planning of a career depends on the position we take on a person, on his ambitions, on his personality.

07:07.000 --> 07:10.000
We can clarify these details during the interview.

07:11.000 --> 07:16.000
Also, in companies, as a rule, now in most companies,

07:16.000 --> 07:24.000
annually or even quarterly, the evaluation of the results of the employee's activity is carried out,

07:24.000 --> 07:28.000
the so-called KPI, with key indicators of efficiency.

07:28.000 --> 07:35.000
And it is very important to position that the result of the employee

07:35.000 --> 07:40.000
will have a serious impact on his career planning and possible promotions.

07:40.000 --> 07:47.000
Employees themselves most often associate the assessment, which in some companies is called attestation,

07:47.000 --> 07:51.000
rather with the payment of bonuses, with a raise in salary,

07:51.000 --> 07:56.000
and rarely think that this can affect their career.

07:56.000 --> 08:00.000
The manager's participation in such interviews,

08:00.000 --> 08:05.000
in the evaluation interview, is very important,

08:05.000 --> 08:14.000
because it is in this interview, in this evaluation conversation of the manager with his subordinate,

08:14.000 --> 08:21.000
that some dissatisfaction with the employee may be revealed regarding his current functionality, current duties.

08:21.000 --> 08:29.000
And new ambitions may be revealed, something that we, for example, did not see half a year ago.

08:29.000 --> 08:33.000
Now the world is changing very quickly, business is changing very quickly.

08:33.000 --> 08:39.000
Our company is in a very energetic changing environment,

08:39.000 --> 08:43.000
and therefore the ideas of employees, their thoughts, their ambitions,

08:43.000 --> 08:46.000
they can change very energetically as well.

08:46.000 --> 08:51.000
And once a quarter, once every six months, this is just the period when it is important to understand

08:51.000 --> 08:56.000
where this employee has advanced, how he suits the company,

08:56.000 --> 09:03.000
where he can be more effective, what additional functionality he is ready to perform and, accordingly, choose for himself.

09:03.000 --> 09:14.000
And usually, I would also recommend in the interview on the assessment of the effectiveness of employees,

09:14.000 --> 09:19.000
include a very important block of planning, training and development.

09:19.000 --> 09:24.000
You can use special forms of the individual development plan,

09:24.000 --> 09:28.000
where we discuss with the employee not only his results for the past period,

09:28.000 --> 09:34.000
but also his plans for the next period, including in terms of responsibility and functions.

09:34.000 --> 09:42.000
And this is just the best time to talk to him about the capabilities of their company in its training and development.

09:42.000 --> 09:47.000
When we talk about training, already looking at the plane of training,

09:47.000 --> 09:58.000
we can say that very often now candidates ask in the job offer to write down what responsibility the company is ready to take

09:58.000 --> 10:03.000
at the stage of negotiations with the future employee about his training.

10:03.000 --> 10:08.000
So, for some employees at certain positions, we can even write that the company,

10:08.000 --> 10:12.000
during the first quarter, the first six months of work,

10:12.000 --> 10:19.000
the first year of work, must train the employee on such topics, on such courses.

10:19.000 --> 10:23.000
And for candidates for work now it has become very significant,

10:23.000 --> 10:30.000
especially those positions that are associated with a certain level of certification,

10:31.000 --> 10:33.000
such as, for example, in the financial sphere.

10:33.000 --> 10:40.000
HR often places this as such an important condition for technical employees, programmers.

10:40.000 --> 10:49.000
And here it is a very serious signal that says that this candidate is serious about his career,

10:49.000 --> 10:59.000
he has certain plans and he considers the work in our company not just as a banal work device,

10:59.000 --> 11:04.000
but also as a way to earn money in the plane of developing his career.

11:04.000 --> 11:14.000
And here, of course, it is also important for us to ask him in more detail what ideas he has in terms of his professional future

11:14.000 --> 11:21.000
and evaluate from the point of view of the employer how long we can be interesting to each other with this employee.

11:21.000 --> 11:29.000
In my experience, it has been meaningful to talk about the horizon of planning for no more than two years.

11:29.000 --> 11:36.000
Usually, candidates consider the possibility of their relationship with a new employer at this time.

11:36.000 --> 11:41.000
And from the point of view of us as employers, this is also a comfortable period

11:41.000 --> 11:51.000
during which we can at least get a ready-to-work candidate in our company.

11:51.000 --> 11:59.000
I usually describe it in such words that you understand that the company will invest its time, its experience in you,

11:59.000 --> 12:06.000
and you will work with colleagues who will share their experience, their technologies.

12:06.000 --> 12:10.000
The company has certain very serious technological developments,

12:10.000 --> 12:18.000
and therefore it would be important for us as a company that you plan your employment with us for at least two years.

12:18.000 --> 12:28.000
And only in this horizon of planning can we discuss our responsibility as an employer in terms of planning a career and in terms of your training.

12:28.000 --> 12:34.000
As a rule, such a horizon of planning is comfortable for the employee and for the company.

12:34.000 --> 12:39.000
In reality, this period is not always withstood.

12:39.000 --> 12:49.000
Some employees work significantly longer, and we have to part with some employees for quite objective reasons.

12:49.000 --> 12:57.000
It is very important not to lower the training plans from top to bottom,

12:57.000 --> 13:07.000
as a big project of the company, but to involve employees in the study, to involve employees in the discussion of the needs of the study.

13:07.000 --> 13:14.000
And we do it in a variety of ways, using all possible reasons for this.

13:14.000 --> 13:23.000
Starting with the reception at work, when we ask such a question for the identification of the interests of the candidates,

13:23.000 --> 13:28.000
we ask such a question as what would you like to learn more about, what training would you like to go through,

13:28.000 --> 13:33.000
what do you think could be interesting to you and would help your efficiency at work.

13:33.000 --> 13:40.000
Also, all interviews with assessments and attestations of employees, assessments of their performance,

13:40.000 --> 13:47.000
they can also serve the purpose of building up plans for the training and development of a person.

13:47.000 --> 13:57.000
But it is also very important to prevent such a consumer attitude of employees to the company.

13:57.000 --> 14:06.000
When an employee peddles the topic that the company should train him, the company should promote him,

14:06.000 --> 14:13.000
it is very important to shift the focus and emphasize that the company also expects from the employee his efforts,

14:13.000 --> 14:16.000
his professional efforts, his self-training.

14:16.000 --> 14:21.000
And training is a mutual process, not a process in one direction.

14:21.000 --> 14:28.000
And in order to increase the responsibility of the employee, we, before expensive training, of course,

14:28.000 --> 14:31.000
sign a student contract with the person.

14:31.000 --> 14:39.000
And besides, we show in a special format how one or another training,

14:39.000 --> 14:44.000
how one or another training should affect the efficiency, the effectiveness of the work of the employee.

14:44.000 --> 14:51.000
And the central, central for the career planning system and for the training system is, of course,

14:51.000 --> 14:53.000
the corporate competence model.

14:53.000 --> 14:57.000
Here on this slide you can see an example of such a model.

14:57.000 --> 15:00.000
Here it consists of 10 competencies.

15:00.000 --> 15:03.000
In each company it can be different.

15:03.000 --> 15:08.000
Competencies can depend on specific positions,

15:08.000 --> 15:13.000
can be developed individually for each group of positions,

15:13.000 --> 15:15.000
or it can be a general corporate model.

15:15.000 --> 15:22.000
It depends on how much time the HR has for its development and at what stage the company is.

15:22.000 --> 15:26.000
But at least one corporate competence model,

15:26.000 --> 15:30.000
which depends on the level of the employee,

15:30.000 --> 15:34.000
depends on their professional specialization, of course, it should be.

15:34.000 --> 15:39.000
Here you see a model of competence out of 10 competencies,

15:39.000 --> 15:44.000
which is designed specifically for a high-tech company working in the field of e-commerce.

15:44.000 --> 15:49.000
The company industry, it imposes a very large imprint,

15:49.000 --> 15:52.000
and greatly affects the composition of the competence.

15:52.000 --> 15:56.000
As you can see, special attention is paid to innovation,

15:56.000 --> 15:59.000
positive thinking, positive communication.

15:59.000 --> 16:03.000
This means that in an innovative company, an innovative industry,

16:03.000 --> 16:05.000
competencies are very important,

16:05.000 --> 16:12.000
which determine the style of communication between employees and the nature of their work.

16:12.000 --> 16:16.000
It is very important for a company that people show innovation,

16:16.000 --> 16:24.000
that they feel free to make decisions and share ideas with each other.

16:25.000 --> 16:29.000
Here you see a very important competence, positive thinking, positive communication.

16:29.000 --> 16:35.000
It is about making it easier for people and employees to share ideas with each other

16:35.000 --> 16:43.000
and to organize working groups to discuss problems or areas of problems

16:43.000 --> 16:49.000
in order to jointly develop a group solution, a group idea.

16:50.000 --> 16:56.000
Here you see that there is a special competence of teamwork, business thinking,

16:56.000 --> 17:05.000
and, of course, professionalism, which depends on the professional field in which a person works.

17:05.000 --> 17:08.000
I would say that this is a universal competence.

17:08.000 --> 17:12.000
Here the manager assesses the employee,

17:12.000 --> 17:23.000
how much his level of knowledge and experience meet the needs of the company.

17:23.000 --> 17:28.000
In the next slide, we can see an example of a bar,

17:28.000 --> 17:31.000
an assessment of key indicators of efficiency.

17:31.000 --> 17:37.000
This is a bar that is used in assessments of the efficiency of employees,

17:37.000 --> 17:43.000
which, as I said, takes place once a quarter, once every six months or once a year, depending on the company.

17:43.000 --> 17:50.000
And here is a very important point that every goal that we set for a person for the next period of work

17:50.000 --> 17:54.000
must be necessarily prescribed, it must be weighted,

17:54.000 --> 17:58.000
it must be assigned a certain weight, a certain importance.

17:58.000 --> 18:06.000
And we must tell the employee what exactly result we expect from him, at what level.

18:06.000 --> 18:13.000
And the most important point is that the employee himself is signed in this bar.

18:13.000 --> 18:17.000
And as a result, after a certain period of time,

18:17.000 --> 18:19.000
this is a quarter, six months or a year,

18:19.000 --> 18:21.000
the employee and the manager meet again,

18:21.000 --> 18:27.000
and they have a great opportunity to assess what goals have been achieved,

18:27.000 --> 18:30.000
achieved at the expected level,

18:30.000 --> 18:35.000
what goals have been achieved, but at a level lower than expected,

18:35.000 --> 18:37.000
what goals have not been achieved, and for what reason.

18:37.000 --> 18:44.000
And this is a great opportunity to assess what we have not achieved,

18:44.000 --> 18:51.000
what prevented us, and what plans in training and development we can offer a person here.

18:51.000 --> 18:56.000
That is, what we as a company can offer an employee in terms of increasing his knowledge,

18:56.000 --> 19:01.000
increasing his experience, his professional competencies.

19:01.000 --> 19:06.000
On the other hand, the employee himself must also think about this.

19:06.000 --> 19:14.000
And, as a rule, employees are already preparing for the assessment of their performance in a few weeks.

19:14.000 --> 19:17.000
And a special training is held in the company,

19:17.000 --> 19:24.000
when we teach managers how to conduct feedback on the results of the assessment of performance.

19:24.000 --> 19:34.000
And we teach the employees how to best use this wonderful opportunity of interview on the results of their activities.

19:34.000 --> 19:40.000
And here on the next slide we can see the simplest format,

19:40.000 --> 19:47.000
which is also used as a result of the interview on the results of the work of the employee.

19:47.000 --> 19:50.000
Here is the individual training plan.

19:50.000 --> 19:55.000
Here we write what the goal of the training is, what we want to train employees for,

19:55.000 --> 20:01.000
the training plan, the topic, the deadlines, and what results we expect.

20:01.000 --> 20:08.000
In addition, here you can also enter a column for which competence a particular training will work.

20:08.000 --> 20:13.000
And this allows us, on the one hand, to plan the training more accurately for the staff.

20:13.000 --> 20:17.000
These blanks are submitted to the training center after the assessment.

20:17.000 --> 20:26.000
And the training center can already assess the needs of the company in training and plan the training for the next period.

20:26.000 --> 20:32.000
And, of course, as you understand, the most effective use of such formats in an electronic form.

20:32.000 --> 20:37.000
And now there are already many programs for managing staff,

20:37.000 --> 20:42.000
which allow you to automate the assessment process of performance,

20:42.000 --> 20:46.000
and planning training, and also planning a career.

20:46.000 --> 20:50.000
So, now let's talk about career planning.

20:50.000 --> 20:55.000
From the point of view of employees, as a rule, career planning is a company's obligation.

20:55.000 --> 21:00.000
What positions should the company offer him at a certain time horizon.

21:00.000 --> 21:04.000
But from the point of view of HR and from the point of view of the company,

21:04.000 --> 21:08.000
career planning is a determination, together with the employee,

21:09.000 --> 21:14.000
to make clear prospects for his professional development within the framework of the company's strategic development.

21:14.000 --> 21:17.000
This is a very important point,

21:17.000 --> 21:24.000
since we plan the career of employees not only based on their ambitions, their professional desires, plans,

21:24.000 --> 21:29.000
but, first of all, of course, from the point of view of the company's strategic plans.

21:29.000 --> 21:32.000
Here you can give such an example.

21:33.000 --> 21:43.000
For example, in one IT company, where the main staff are software specialists and software implementation,

21:43.000 --> 21:52.000
when the company changed its strategy and changed the focus of its activities from software development to its implementation,

21:52.000 --> 21:59.000
we conducted a special interview with each programmer on the subject of his interests, his ambitions,

21:59.000 --> 22:09.000
and used different levers, different methods to help programmers realize how interesting it would be for them,

22:09.000 --> 22:13.000
that it would be interesting for them not only to program and work with code,

22:13.000 --> 22:18.000
but also to work with the client and implement software products.

22:18.000 --> 22:22.000
Of course, we understand the limitations of this approach,

22:22.000 --> 22:26.000
that there are programmers who do not want to see the client in principle,

22:27.000 --> 22:35.000
but there are also a certain number of programmers who are ready to consider the possibility of working with clients at a certain time horizon

22:35.000 --> 22:43.000
and can see how the client's work on the implementation of software products, how it promotes them professionally.

22:43.000 --> 22:51.000
And here it is very important for us, as HR, to be able to argue this position, which is very important for the company,

22:51.000 --> 22:54.000
and can also be beneficial for the employees themselves,

22:54.000 --> 23:01.000
because they will be able to further develop within the company and develop their professional skills and knowledge.

23:01.000 --> 23:08.000
That is, our main goal in planning a career is to create a synergy of interests of the company and the employee,

23:08.000 --> 23:16.000
which is achieved through numerous negotiations, numerous interviews and numerous methods of managing staff.

23:17.000 --> 23:21.000
Thus, with the help of planning a career, we solve several tasks at once.

23:21.000 --> 23:23.000
This is not material motivation.

23:23.000 --> 23:27.000
It would seem that this is paradoxical, but nevertheless,

23:27.000 --> 23:32.000
simply because the manager of the staff, the head of the employee,

23:32.000 --> 23:38.000
once a quarter or once every six months, talks to the employee and discusses his ambitions,

23:38.000 --> 23:42.000
his professional goals, his needs in training and development,

23:42.000 --> 23:48.000
only one of these facts already reduces the tension in the team

23:48.000 --> 23:56.000
and gives the employees a clearer perspective of their professional path in the company.

23:56.000 --> 23:59.000
This significantly affects motivation.

23:59.000 --> 24:05.000
We also achieve the reduction of liquidity by planning a career,

24:05.000 --> 24:12.000
because employees who see their prospects in the company are less likely to leave the competition,

24:12.000 --> 24:16.000
since they see their opportunities with us.

24:16.000 --> 24:21.000
In addition, employees work more energetically, more motivatedly.

24:21.000 --> 24:27.000
That is, in the same time, with the help of the same resources, we achieve a greater result.

24:27.000 --> 24:34.000
Therefore, I would say that planning a career is such a universal tool and a very powerful tool.

24:34.000 --> 24:39.000
The only thing is that certain resources are necessary here.

24:39.000 --> 24:50.000
In the next slide, we can see a pyramid that shows how different companies are moving towards this topic.

24:50.000 --> 24:58.000
At the first level, the number K1, it shows that many companies are thinking about planning a career

24:58.000 --> 25:06.000
only when an employee comes with his application and says about his intention to leave the company.

25:06.000 --> 25:12.000
Then the boss calls HR manager and says, listen, talk to him, maybe you will offer him something,

25:12.000 --> 25:14.000
or let's think together.

25:14.000 --> 25:21.000
This is such a natural solution to the problem of planning a career.

25:22.000 --> 25:28.000
Further, at the second stage, management, after a certain number of such cases,

25:28.000 --> 25:36.000
when employees want to leave, but the reason is not only money, but also career prospects,

25:36.000 --> 25:38.000
the management sets us a goal.

25:38.000 --> 25:45.000
Let's somehow describe how our employees can develop within the company.

25:45.000 --> 25:50.000
In fact, this is a very difficult technological task, very difficult.

25:50.000 --> 25:55.000
It is very important to analyze the entire organizational structure,

25:55.000 --> 26:01.000
taking into account the fact that employees can grow their careers not only in their management vertical,

26:01.000 --> 26:07.000
but it is also important to highlight the entire blocks of the organizational structure,

26:07.000 --> 26:15.000
